    "body": "## Problem\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nlocal api, fn = vim.api, vim.fn\nvim.cmd('new')\nvim.cmd('wincmd w')\napi.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, true, { 'a', 'b' })\napi.nvim_win_set_cursor(0, { 2, 0 })\napi.nvim_feedkeys(api.nvim_replace_termcodes('<C-q>', true, false, true), 'x', false)\n-- vim.cmd('wincmd w') -- good\napi.nvim_set_current_win(fn.win_getid(fn.winnr('#')))\nvim.cmd.redraw() -- E315: ml_get: Invalid lnum: 2\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\nno ml_get error on redraw\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.12.0-dev-1877 ge1aceb0068` neovim/neovim@e1aceb0068\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.17.9-zen1-1-zen\n- Terminal name/version: kitty\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-kitty`\n- Installation: ?\n\n",
